display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be a field. An <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-000T.xml"
addr="nt-000T"
title="Algebraic Element">algebraic extension</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {L} / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> is called an <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Algebraic Closure</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> if every polynomial <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)\in \mathbb {F}[x]]]></fr:tex> splits completely over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {L}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p><fr:strong>Notation:</fr:strong> We typically denote the algebraic closure of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> with an overline <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\overline {\mathbb {F}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
